extends layout.pug

block content 
  article.grid-container.portfolio-intro
    div

      //- Add a title or heading like My Portfolio, or Hey, Potential Employers, or Let's make the web great together! 
      h1 My collection of websites I have done

      //- Add a description for your portfolio, what this project is, it's purpose, what it's supposed to accomplish, etc. 
      p.lead.text-light
        | This is my portfolio that shows my current skill set. I am also currently learning about React and I really am excited in learning how to make apps
  article.grid-container.portfolio-index
    
    .grid-x.grid-margin-x.small-up-2.medium-up-2.large-up-3
      //- Use the Pug `each` iterator to create a project img, title and link in the markup for each of the projects you are showcasing.  
      
      //- Use a combination of interpolation and template literals as needed to dynamically generate the routes in the href, as well as the img's src and the projects title.
      
      //- Here's what the Pug for each project example should look like. 
      
      //-iterate through each index of data.projects and update properties using interpolation.
      //-I received help on this section from myles young
    -const data = data.projects
      each val, index in data
        a(href=`/project/${val.id}`)
          img.thumbnail(src=`${val.image_urls[0]}`)
          h5 #{val.project_name}

      